cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.NE 

The paper discusses the robustness of neural networks and adversarial training, which are topics commonly studied in the sub-fields of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of Lipschitz classifiers and optimal transport theory also suggests a connection to the sub-field of neural engineering (cs.NE).
